@page "/faq"

<PageTitle>Frequently Asked Questions</PageTitle>

<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Large" Class="my-16">
    <MudText Typo="Typo.h3" GutterBottom>Frequently Asked Questions</MudText>

    <MudExpansionPanels>
        <MudExpansionPanel Text="What is Borderless Minecraft?">

        </MudExpansionPanel>
        <MudExpansionPanel Text="Is Borderless Minecraft Free?">
            Yes! Borderless Minecraft is free and open source. This means the code can be downloaded and even modified by anyone.
        </MudExpansionPanel>
        <MudExpansionPanel Text="Why are admin rights required for auto borderless?">
            Detecting when a process starts requires higher privilages than running an app.
        </MudExpansionPanel>
        <MudExpansionPanel Text="Why does windows say the publisher is unknown?">
            Verifying code is an expensive process that I cannot justify at this time. However, the code is open source and can be viewed by anyone for safety.
        </MudExpansionPanel>
        <MudExpansionPanel Text="I'm having an issue! Where can I report it?">
            Create an issue on <MudLink Href="https://github.com/Mr-Technician/BorderlessMinecraft/issues" Target="_blank">Github</MudLink> and I will take a look.
        </MudExpansionPanel>
        <MudExpansionPanel Text="Can I contribute to Borderless Minecraft?">
            Yes! Open the repository on <MudLink Href="https://github.com/Mr-Technician/BorderlessMinecraft" Target="_blank">Github</MudLink>, fork the code, make changes, and open a pull request.
        </MudExpansionPanel>
    </MudExpansionPanels>
</MudContainer>

